Summarise each of the {n} numbered texts below into a memory record that the user will be able to ask questions about later.

## Preserve EVERY fact (PER TEXT)
Your job is to preserve every concrete piece of information the text contains, especially:
- **Personal facts about the user**: degree, age, family members, job, employer, hobbies, location, preferences, decisions stated, actions taken, events attended.
- **Proper nouns**: brand names, places, people, organisations, products.
- **Specific numbers and dates**: amounts, prices, ages, dates, counts.
- **Implied facts**: if the user says 'when I graduated', they graduated; if they say 'my wife', they have a wife.

## Bias toward user facts over generic content
If a text mixes a personal fact with a list of recommendations or generic advice, the personal fact is MORE important. Drop generic advice before dropping a personal detail.

## Length
Each summary: 2–4 sentences. Dense with facts, no filler, no preamble like 'This text discusses...'.

## Output format
Return ONLY a JSON array of exactly {n} strings, one per numbered text, in order. No markdown fences, no trailing commentary, no keys — just the array.

## Texts to summarise
{numbered}
